Important Note: Used colabfold to generate structure. Possible alpha fold and pdb structure are the correct protein, and the PDB id is mentioned in the paper. However, they are both missing the end of the sequence relative to DMS and alignment, because "The Bgl3 construct has 500 amino acid positions." Whereas the structures have 479.

Romero et al. Dissecting enzyme function with microfluidic-based deep mutational scanning, Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences. 2015. https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.1422285112
The paper studies beta glucosidase from Streptomyces sp, and one of the reasons is that it "has been solved to high resolution". So, I feel somewhat confident about 1GNX being a good structure.
